  "prompt": "Can you go on both Kickstarter and Indiegogo at the same time? What are some of the companies who have done it, concurrently or sequentially?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to run crowdfunding campaigns on both Kickstarter and Indiegogo simultaneously or sequentially. Many companies have used this strategy to maximize their funding potential and reach different audiences. Here are some examples:\n\nCompanies that have used both platforms:\n\n1. Pebble Smartwatch\n- Kickstarter campaign: Raised over $10 million\n- Later campaigns on Indiegogo\n\n2. Exploding Kittens (Card Game)\n- Successfully ran campaigns on both platforms\n\n3. OUYA Gaming Console\n- Kickstarter campaign first\n- Later Indiegogo campaign\n\n4. Peak Design (Camera Accessories)\n- Multiple successful campaigns on both platforms\n\n5. Coolest Cooler\n- Initially successful on Kickstarter\n- Returned on Indiegogo after initial campaign\n\nStrategies for using multiple platforms:\n- Sequential campaigns\n- Simultaneous campaigns\n- Platform-specific stretch goals\n- Targeting different audience segments\n\nConsiderations:\n- Different platform fees\n- Unique audience demographics\n- Platform-specific rules and restrictions\n- Potential donor fatigue\n\nWhile possible, it's important to carefully plan and execute multi-platform crowdfunding strategies.",
